04/07/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- New High Representative Miroslav Lajcak held his first meeting Tuesday (July 3rd) with BiH Prime Minister Nikola Spiric and deputies Dragan Vrankic and Tarik Sadovic. After the talks, Spiric said what began as a protocol meeting turned into a working one, with Lajcak saying he does not want to lose more time. They discussed unresolved political issues and the challenges facing the country on the road to the EU, agreeing to establish daily communications between their offices. (Nezavisne Novine, Dnevni Avaz - 04/07/07; RTRS, Fena, NTV Hayat - 03/07/07) 
